# Line-ending policy for sdk-ios.
#
# NOTE: .gitattributes do not cross repository boundaries, so this submodule does
# not inherit the workspace-root .gitattributes. It needs its own.
#
# Git for Windows ships core.autocrlf=true as a SYSTEM default
# (C:/Program Files/Git/etc/gitconfig), which checks text files out as CRLF on a
# fresh Windows clone.
#
# scripts/build-xcframework.sh and scripts/release-apple.sh are POSIX shell scripts
# that run on a Mac (they build the AttriaxCore XCFramework from sdk-kmp's Apple
# targets and cut the release). A CRLF checkout gives them a `#!/bin/sh\r` shebang,
# which fails with an obscure "no such file or directory".
#
# This matters MORE here than elsewhere, not less: this repo is authored on Windows
# but its scripts only ever execute on a Mac, so nobody on the authoring machine
# would notice a CRLF checkout until the Mac pass fails. This repo currently carries
# a local `core.autocrlf=false`, but local config is machine-local and never travels
# with the repo — the Mac clone gets the system default. This attribute travels.
#
# Deliberately targeted: the Swift facade is hand-written with no LF-regenerating
# tooling, and the vendored AttriaxCore.xcframework is git-ignored, so a blanket
# `* text=auto eol=lf` would buy nothing.
*.sh text eol=lf
